===Noun===
{{en-noun|coal|coals}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} A black rock formed from [[prehistoric]] plant [[remains]], composed largely of [[carbon]] and burned as a fuel.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A piece of coal used for burning. Note that in British English the first of the following examples could be used, whereas in both British and American English the latter would.
#: ''Put some '''coals''' on the fire.''
#: ''Put some '''coal''' on the fire.''
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A type of coal, such as [[bituminous]], [[anthracite]], or [[lignite]], and grades and varieties thereof.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A smouldering piece of material.
#: ''Just as the camp-fire died down to just '''coals''', with no flames to burn the marshmallows, someone dumped a whole load of wood on, so I gave up and went to bed.''

